<subSubSection id="FAD0AAB4EC6F8C30FF54F84CFB5AFE3D" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B275F93FEC6F8C30FF54F84CFB5AFE3D" blockId="1.[151,1436,1988,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6F8C33FF54F84CFEB6F84D" bold="true" box="[151,273,1988,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species keys nearest to 
<taxonomicName id="75CA82BCEC6F8C33FD98F84CFBA6F84D" authority="Efflatoun, 1945" authorityName="Efflatoun" authorityYear="1945" box="[603,1025,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salmayensis">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6F8C33FD98F84CFCE0F84C" box="[603,839,1988,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Phthiria salmayensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D65B84CEEC6F8C33FC8CF84CFBA6F84D" author="Efflatoun" box="[847,1025,1988,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refString="Efflatoun, H. C. (1945) A monograph of Egyptian Diptera. Part VI. Family Bombyliidae. Section 1: Subfamily Bombyliidae Homeophthalmae. Bulletin de la Societ Fouad I er d'Entomologie, 29, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1945">
Efflatoun, 
<number id="0402EB18EC6F8C33FC04F84CFBA6F84D" box="[967,1025,1988,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" value="1945.0">1945</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, using Efflatoun’s (
<number id="0402EB18EC6F8C33FB1DF84CFABFF84D" box="[1246,1304,1988,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" value="1945.0">1945</number>
) key, but is differentiated from it by the darker appearance especially in the male; the black hairs at the sides of the abdominal tergites; and the shape and structure of genitalia that in 
<taxonomicName id="75CA82BCEC6C8C30FD3CFF34FC14FF44" box="[767,947,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharafi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FD3CFF34FC14FF44" box="[767,947,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Phthiria sharafi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9B8D9856EC6C8C30FC7AFF34FBB4FF45" box="[953,1043,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" rank="species">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FC7AFF34FBB4FF45" bold="true" box="[953,1043,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="2AF1E5BAEC6C8C30FBE1FF34FB2BFF44" box="[1058,1164,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,200,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[192,1394,193,1238]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 9. Male Genitalia: 6. Phthiria salmayensis Efflatoun, 1945, ventral view; 7. Phthiria sharafi sp. nov., ventral view; 8. same, lateral view; 9. same, aedeagal tip, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226942/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Figs. 
<number id="0402EB18EC6C8C30FBA3FF34FB2BFF44" box="[1120,1164,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
</figureCitation>
) has gonocoxites longer than broad, with subparallel sides and their posterior processes two times as long as broad with hairs sparse, few, weak and located mainly at their tips; the narrow distiphallus is about third the length of the thick basiphallus; also the lateral epiphallic process (
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FDC2FEA1FD98FED0" box="[513,575,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">sensu</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="D65B84CEEC6C8C30FD97FEAFFCADFED0" author="Evenhuis" box="[596,778,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (1990) Systematics and evolution of the genera of the subfamilies Usiinae and Phthiriinae of the world (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Entomonograph, 11, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1990">
Evenhuis, 
<number id="0402EB18EC6C8C30FD12FEA0FCADFED0" box="[721,778,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) is undulated. However in 
<taxonomicName id="75CA82BCEC6C8C30FB98FEA1FAA3FED0" box="[1115,1284,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salmayensis">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FB98FEA1FAA3FED0" box="[1115,1284,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">P. salmayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="2AF1E5BAEC6C8C30FAD9FEAFFAC4FED0" box="[1306,1379,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,200,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[192,1394,193,1238]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 9. Male Genitalia: 6. Phthiria salmayensis Efflatoun, 1945, ventral view; 7. Phthiria sharafi sp. nov., ventral view; 8. same, lateral view; 9. same, aedeagal tip, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226942/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Fig. 
<number id="0402EB18EC6C8C30FA97FEAFFAC4FED0" box="[1364,1379,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) the gonocoxites are as broad as or broader than long, barrel-shaped, with the posterior processes approximately as long as or slightly longer than broad; coarse black hairs cover all the posterior processes; the narrow distiphallus is only about one fifth the length of the thick basiphallus; and the lateral epiphallic process is not undulated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FAD0AAB4EC6C8C30FF04FE3FFE95FD88" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B275F93FEC6C8C30FF04FE3FFE95FD88" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FF04FE3FFEE9FE40" bold="true" box="[199,334,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Etymology.</emphasis>
The patronymic name 
<taxonomicName id="75CA82BCEC6C8C30FD9CFE30FD09FE40" box="[607,686,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharafi">
<emphasis id="80BE252DEC6C8C30FD9CFE30FD09FE40" box="[607,686,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">sharafi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed in honor of our colleague Dr Mostafa Sharaf, Plant Protection Department, College of Food and Agriculture Sciences, King Saud University, Riyadh, 
<collectingCountry id="CADDB9AFEC6C8C30FAD2FE54FE8AFD88" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Kingdom of Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
